    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-09-24T11:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-09-24T11:30:00-05:00" n="882"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d882">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">211.31/9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McGoodwin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-09-24T12:00:00-04:30">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1921—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received September 28—4:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Department’s telegram June 25, 4 p.m.<note n="7" xml:id="d882fn7">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Draft of treaty with Honduras finally accepted adding to paragraph inserted
                    Department’s instruction number 550 imprisonment [for life<note n="8"
                        xml:id="d882fn8">The words “for life” supplied from the Minister’s despatch
                        no. 2517 of the same date (file no. 211.31/10).</note>], prohibited by
                    constitution. Please answer by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McGoodwin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
